{{Quote|Is that the Blackwater?|[[Arya Stark]] to [[Sandor Clegane]]|Second Sons (episode)}}
The '''Blackwater Rush''', also called the '''Blackwater''' or '''River Blackwater''', is a significant river of [[Westeros]]. It flows out of the hills and valleys of the [[Westerlands]] and proceeds eastwards for several hundred miles before flowing into [[Blackwater Bay]]. The city of [[King's Landing]] overlooks the mouth of the Blackwater. A tributary of the Blackwater feeds the lake of [[Gods Eye]] to the north.&lt;ref name=&quot;Viewers Guide&quot;&gt;[http://viewers-guide.hbo.com/game-of-thrones/season2/#!/locations/kings-landing/ HBO viewers guide, season 2 map, King's Landing entry]&lt;/ref&gt;

The town of [[Stoney Sept]] is located not far from its headwaters.
